I'll help you create a React user profile card component. Here's a clean implementation:

```jsx
import React from 'react';
import './UserProfile.css';

const UserProfile = ({ user }) => {
  const { avatar, name, bio } = user;

  return (
    <div className="user-profile-card">
      <img 
        src={avatar} 
        alt={`${name}'s avatar`}
        className="avatar"
      />
      <h2 className="name">{name}</h2>
      <p className="bio">{bio}</p>
    </div>
  );
};

export default UserProfile;
```

And here's the accompanying CSS:

```css
.user-profile-card {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 20px;
  border-radius: 8px;
  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  max-width: 300px;
  background: white;
}

.avatar {
  width: 80px;
  height: 80px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  object-fit: cover;
  margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.name {
  margin: 0 0 8px 0;
  font-size: 1.2em;
  color: #333;
}

.bio {
  margin: 0;
  text-align: center;
  color: #666;
  line-height: 1.4;
}
```

Great question! Here are some responsive improvements you can add to the CSS:

```css
.user-profile-card {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 20px;
  border-radius: 8px;
  box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  max-width: 300px;
  width: 100%;
  background: white;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* Mobile responsive styles */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .user-profile-card {
    max-width: 100%;
    margin: 0 16px;
    padding: 16px;
  }

  .avatar {
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
  }

  .name {
    font-size: 1.1em;
  }

  .bio {
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }
}
```

Key responsive improvements:
1. Added `width: 100%` and `box-sizing: border-box`
2. Mobile media query for screens under 768px
3. Smaller avatar and text sizes on mobile
4. Reduced padding and margins for better mobile UX
